occurrenceRemarks: One male with three females found inside a still-ripening apple that had apparently been scooped previously by possibly birds or voles (voles have been a problem here the past year). Other scooped apples contained mostly earwigs and some ants. Important to note, we also had extremely productive blueberries nearby this year with no Drosophila problems noticed. I am now keeping a closer eye (even more than usual) on certain trees at the nursery because a hopefully isolated incident of spotted lanternfly was recently discovered in an unknown place in the city. I really wish the exact location would be disclosed so that we could have a possible idea of where they hitchhiked from, so that we do not receive shipments from there. But instead I will just have to be extra diligent.
